Temperature Menu
Click again to go to Heating Mode.

Heating Mode Menu
Click again to go to Heating Mode.

Switching to Ready Mode
This mode allows the heater to heat, at all times, in order to maintain the preset temperature.
Indicated by the Ready Mode "R" icon on the Main Menu Display.
Pump 1 low speed activates periodically to circulate the water and determine the spa temperature.

Switching to Rest Mode
This mode allows the heater to heat only during a programmed filter cycle.
Indicated by the Rest Mode "R"(sideways) icon on the Main Menu display.
If the primary pump has not turned on within an hour, the message "RUN PUMP FOR TEMP" will appear on the display.
Pressing the Jets Pump 2 button will activate the pump and heater so the temperature can be sensed and displayed.
